description.value:
Plastic box (with yellow label '66') with transparent lid containing a fragments of papyrus. 'Coptic' is written on the lid in yellow crayon. A label by Stephen Quirke reads '13 Greek or Coptic fragments; 1 fragment Demotic. Stored at back of Pap. Room (15/1/92). Box marked "Coptic" in yellow, like "Hibeh" fragments'.
The fragments inside are unmounted and unglazed.
